{
  "texts": [
    "The idea of AI systems with Agency stems from the discourse surrounding the development of autonomous intelligent agents capable of mimicking human-like behavior and decision-making (Harrell and Zhu, 2009; Wen and Imamizu, 2022).",
    "Agency drives how an agent contributes to a given task.",
    "In settings like games or AI-assisted teaching, AI may be the one guiding the task (e.g., as a non-character player).",
    "Also, in creative applications, engaging with a reactive AI without intention, motivation, and goals may be perceived as less meaningful.",
    "The ideal Agency of an agent would be defined by the task/application."
  ]
}